<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Privacy Policy - Daily Affirmations</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #f7f4ff;
      --card: #ffffff;
      --text: #222222;
      --muted: #666666;
      --accent: #7c4dff;
      --border: #e9e1ff;
    }

    * { box-sizing: border-box; }

    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #f7f4ff 0%, #fcfbff 100%);
      color: var(--text);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .wrap {
      max-width: 860px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 32px 20px 60px;
    }

    .card {
      background: var(--card);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 20px;
      padding: 32px;
      box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(124, 77, 255, 0.08);
    }

    h1 {
      margin: 0 0 8px;
      font-size: 2rem;
      color: var(--accent);
    }

    h2 {
      margin-top: 28px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      font-size: 1.2rem;
    }

    p, li {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .muted {
      color: var(--muted);
      margin-bottom: 24px;
    }

    ul {
      padding-left: 20px;
    }

    .email {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 10px 14px;
      border-radius: 12px;
      background: #f3edff;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      color: var(--accent);
      font-weight: bold;
      text-decoration: none;
      word-break: break-all;
    }

    .footer {
      margin-top: 24px;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .card {
        padding: 22px;
        border-radius: 16px;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 1.6rem;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="card">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="muted"><strong>App:</strong> Daily Affirmations – Motivation &amp; Confidence<br><strong>Last Updated:</strong> March 10, 2026</p>

      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how the mobile application <strong>Daily Affirmations – Motivation &amp; Confidence</strong>
        (the “App”) handles information when you use it.
      </p>

      <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        The App is designed to provide daily affirmations and motivational content. At this time, the App does not require
        account creation and does not directly collect personal information such as your name, email address, phone number,
        or precise location.
      </p>

      <h2>Advertising</h2>
      <p>
        The App may display advertising through third-party services, such as Google AdMob. These services may automatically
        collect limited information such as device information, advertising identifiers, approximate location, and app usage
        data in order to provide and improve advertising.
      </p>

      <h2>How Information Is Used</h2>
      <p>Automatically collected information may be used for the following purposes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>To provide and improve the App experience</li>
        <li>To display advertisements</li>
        <li>To analyze general app usage trends</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        The App may rely on third-party services that may collect information in accordance with their own privacy policies,
        including advertising and analytics providers.
      </p>

      <h2>Data Security</h2>
      <p>
        We value your trust and take reasonable steps to protect information associated with the App. However, no method of
        electronic transmission or storage is completely secure.
      </p>

      <h2>Children’s Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        The App is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable
        information from children under 13. If you believe such information has been provided, please contact us.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated
        effective date.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you can contact the developer at:</p>
      <p><a class="email" href="mailto:youremail@example.com">youremail@example.com</a></p>

      <p class="footer">
        Replace the contact email above before publishing. You can host this file on GitHub Pages, Netlify, or any basic web host,
        then paste the public URL into your Google Play privacy policy field.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
